1
00:00:08,921 --> 00:00:09,717
<i>C'mon!</i>

2
00:00:16,061 --> 00:00:18,689
<i>Running like a fugitive,</i>

3
00:00:19,732 --> 00:00:21,893
<i>Being chased by something</i>

4
00:00:23,569 --> 00:00:26,231
<i>Inside my heart is pounding</i>

5
00:00:27,339 --> 00:00:29,967
<i>My throat dry like it's withering</i>

6
00:00:31,677 --> 00:00:34,771
<i>For no single one,</i>

7
00:00:35,414 --> 00:00:38,542
<i>To none does belong,</i>

8
00:00:40,019 --> 00:00:44,388
<i>This time is ours, right now...</i>

9
00:00:47,026 --> 00:00:48,789
<i>Unraveling the pain,</i>

10
00:00:48,894 --> 00:00:50,623
<i>Unraveling our hearts,</i>

11
00:00:50,696 --> 00:00:53,028
<i>Unraveling shadows</i>

12
00:00:54,567 --> 00:00:56,330
<i>Stifling our breath,</i>

13
00:00:56,402 --> 00:00:58,302
<i>Reaching for beyond,</i>

14
00:00:58,370 --> 00:01:00,804
<i>Tearing through the dark</i>

15
00:01:02,708 --> 00:01:09,272
<i>In fighting and in love</i>

16
00:01:10,382 --> 00:01:12,873
<i>To the distant light above,</i>

17
00:01:13,652 --> 00:01:16,519
<i>Yes, we are on the way</i>

18
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:22,657
<i>I wanna rock...</i>

19
00:01:25,130 --> 00:01:26,654
<i>Rockin' my heart</i>

20
00:01:32,315 --> 00:01:34,476
Is this the first time you
have faced a friend's death?

21
00:01:36,219 --> 00:01:38,585
This is the way of the Shinobi...

22
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:44,925
I won't forgive you...

23
00:02:05,048 --> 00:02:06,675
I'm going to kill you!

24
00:02:31,041 --> 00:02:36,911
<i>White Past. Hidden Ambition</i>

25
00:02:43,186 --> 00:02:44,346
<i>There's murder in his eyes!</i>

26
00:02:44,821 --> 00:02:46,914
<i>He looks nothing like he used to!</i>

27
00:02:48,925 --> 00:02:49,653
<i>He's coming!</i>

28
00:02:54,564 --> 00:02:55,258
<i>What?</i>

29
00:02:57,667 --> 00:02:59,191
<i>His Chakra repelled my attack!</i>

30
00:03:00,170 --> 00:03:01,262
<i>Then...</i>

31
00:03:13,316 --> 00:03:14,340
<i>This should do it!</i>

32
00:03:20,390 --> 00:03:21,288
<i>Why?!</i>

33
00:03:25,829 --> 00:03:26,693
<i>It can't be!</i>

34
00:03:32,936 --> 00:03:35,336
<i>Could... Naruto's seal</i>
<i>have been broken...?!</i>

35
00:03:37,273 --> 00:03:38,137
<i>No.</i>

36
00:03:38,208 --> 00:03:39,197
<i>This feeling...</i>

37
00:03:40,477 --> 00:03:42,240
<i>True, the seal is almost off</i>

38
00:03:42,545 --> 00:03:45,708
<i>and the Chakra of the Nine Tailed</i>
<i>Fox Spirit is escaping, but...</i>

39
00:03:47,617 --> 00:03:50,484
<i>Fortunately, the seal is not</i>
<i>completely broken!</i>

40
00:03:52,922 --> 00:03:54,514
<i>I still have some time!</i>

41
00:03:56,659 --> 00:03:57,819
Do you hear me, Zabuza?

42
00:03:58,528 --> 00:03:59,893
We're both busy people.

43
00:04:00,897 --> 00:04:02,831
I know it's against your style,

44
00:04:03,299 --> 00:04:05,893
but I think it's about time
we stopped playing around.

45
00:04:09,205 --> 00:04:11,639
Why don't we settle this once
and for all with the next move?

46
00:04:12,242 --> 00:04:13,470
Interesting.

47
00:04:14,177 --> 00:04:16,941
What can you possibly
do in this situation?

48
00:04:17,347 --> 00:04:19,713
Kakashi, go ahead.
Show me.

49
00:04:26,723 --> 00:04:27,587
<i>No good...</i>

50
00:04:27,657 --> 00:04:29,921
<i>I can't hold his aura down!</i>

51
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,629
<i>Zabuza...</i>

52
00:05:21,611 --> 00:05:24,842
<i>I can't defeat this boy.</i>

53
00:05:28,618 --> 00:05:29,550
<i>Zabuza...</i>

54
00:05:33,389 --> 00:05:34,185
<i>I'm...</i>

55
00:06:03,853 --> 00:06:06,686
You... from that time...

56
00:06:08,825 --> 00:06:09,621
Why?

57
00:06:09,926 --> 00:06:10,893
Why stop?

58
00:06:12,428 --> 00:06:18,628
Even though I killed your dear friend,
you can't kill me?

59
00:06:27,443 --> 00:06:28,410
Damn it!

60
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:38,885
What happened to the
force from moment ago?

61
00:06:39,656 --> 00:06:44,559
You can't defeat me with
that kind of strength.

62
00:06:45,795 --> 00:06:48,821
Wasn't he someone
special to you?

63
00:06:50,933 --> 00:06:53,731
<i>Is there someone special</i>
<i>in your life?</i>

64
00:06:55,104 --> 00:06:57,197
<i>I want to protect someone</i>
<i>special to me.</i>

65
00:06:57,940 --> 00:07:00,204
<i>I want to make that</i>
<i>person's dream a reality...</i>

66
00:07:00,977 --> 00:07:02,444
<i>That's my dream.</i>

67
00:07:04,347 --> 00:07:07,839
Many people misunderstand.

68
00:07:09,152 --> 00:07:12,644
They pity and don't finish off
the enemy they ought to finish.

69
00:07:12,889 --> 00:07:15,016
They let them survive.

70
00:07:16,626 --> 00:07:20,858
To me, that isn't compassion
or anything.

71
00:07:23,232 --> 00:07:24,164
Do you know?

72
00:07:25,068 --> 00:07:28,333
How it feels to
not be needed by anyone?

73
00:07:29,105 --> 00:07:32,131
To live day to day without a dream.
The pain of it all.

74
00:07:33,242 --> 00:07:34,675
What are you saying?

75
00:07:35,278 --> 00:07:39,408
Zabuza has no use
for a weak Shinobi.

76
00:07:39,816 --> 00:07:43,081
You took away
my reason for existence.

77
00:07:44,153 --> 00:07:45,085
Why?

78
00:07:45,355 --> 00:07:47,289
Why do you have to
serve a guy like that?

79
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:51,417
He gets the money from thugs
to do bad things!

80
00:07:51,861 --> 00:07:56,298
Is that No Brow
the only person special to you?

81
00:07:58,234 --> 00:08:01,897
A long time ago,
I had other people special to me.

82
00:08:03,940 --> 00:08:07,034
They were... my parents.

83
00:08:10,279 --> 00:08:15,911
I was born in the Land of Water,
in a small village heavy with snow.

84
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:19,617
My parents worked on a small farm.

85
00:08:19,689 --> 00:08:21,782
We were very poor,

86
00:08:22,225 --> 00:08:25,160
but my parents seem to
be satisfied with it.

87
00:08:27,263 --> 00:08:28,787
I was happy then...

88
00:08:29,332 --> 00:08:31,493
They were loving parents.

89
00:08:34,203 --> 00:08:35,033
But...

90
00:08:35,872 --> 00:08:37,931
When I was old enough
to understand things,

91
00:08:38,775 --> 00:08:40,606
something happened.

92
00:08:41,177 --> 00:08:42,144
Something?

93
00:08:42,578 --> 00:08:44,045
What happened?

94
00:08:50,686 --> 00:08:51,880
My blood...

95
00:08:52,522 --> 00:08:53,420
Blood?

96
00:08:56,025 --> 00:08:57,014
Go on!

97
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:59,624
Tell me what happened.

98
00:09:01,831 --> 00:09:04,299
My father...
He killed my mother.

99
00:09:04,901 --> 00:09:07,062
Then he tried to kill me.

100
00:09:07,470 --> 00:09:08,368
Huh?!

101
00:09:10,873 --> 00:09:14,138
After the experience of
the ceaseless civil war,

102
00:09:14,444 --> 00:09:18,574
people with Kekkei Genkai were
hated and feared in the Land of Water.

103
00:09:19,215 --> 00:09:20,978
Kekkei Genkai?

104
00:09:21,684 --> 00:09:25,586
It's special powers or Jutsu
passed on through certain clans,

105
00:09:25,655 --> 00:09:30,718
from parent to child,
or from grandparent to grandchild.

106
00:09:31,794 --> 00:09:34,319
Because of their special powers,

107
00:09:34,897 --> 00:09:38,924
those of the clans were exploited in
all sorts of battles.

108
00:09:39,001 --> 00:09:41,663
As a result, all Kekkei Genkai
were feared

109
00:09:41,737 --> 00:09:44,331
as harbingers of disaster
and death.

110
00:09:49,045 --> 00:09:50,273
After the war was over,

111
00:09:50,346 --> 00:09:55,113
they decided to hide
their special powers.

112
00:09:56,185 --> 00:10:01,350
If anyone knew of their secret,
only death could be expected.

113
00:10:02,792 --> 00:10:06,819
I'm sure that boy went through
so much suffering as well.

114
00:10:07,663 --> 00:10:11,497
The greater your power,
the more you were feared.

115
00:10:13,536 --> 00:10:17,233
My mother had the Kekkei Genkai.

116
00:10:17,940 --> 00:10:20,408
She kept it secret from my father.

117
00:10:20,910 --> 00:10:22,309
She hoped that for a while...

118
00:10:22,378 --> 00:10:27,179
No, she must have thought that
they could have a simple life forever.

119
00:10:33,089 --> 00:10:35,421
<i>Look, Mommy! Look!</i>

120
00:10:36,659 --> 00:10:38,718
<i>Isn't it fantastic?</i>

121
00:10:41,197 --> 00:10:42,596
<i>Not you, too!</i>

122
00:10:42,698 --> 00:10:44,723
<i>Why? Why him, too?</i>

123
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:45,732
<i>That hurts, Mommy!</i>

124
00:10:52,141 --> 00:10:53,108
<i>Sorry...</i>

125
00:10:53,276 --> 00:10:55,767
<i>I'm sorry, Haku...</i>

126
00:10:57,113 --> 00:10:58,444
<i>I'm sorry!</i>

127
00:11:00,917 --> 00:11:02,043
However...

128
00:11:02,218 --> 00:11:06,177
Father had discovered our secret.

129
00:12:06,649 --> 00:12:07,911
When I came to...

130
00:12:08,351 --> 00:12:10,683
I had killed my own father.

131
00:12:12,755 --> 00:12:17,215
And that moment,
what I thought of myself was that...

132
00:12:18,928 --> 00:12:20,555
no, that is what I had to think.

133
00:12:23,165 --> 00:12:25,759
And then knew that it was
the most painful thing.

134
00:12:26,435 --> 00:12:28,801
The most... painful thing...?

135
00:12:30,306 --> 00:12:31,364
That I...

136
00:12:31,641 --> 00:12:36,510
that my existence didn't matter
to anyone else in the world.

137
00:12:37,747 --> 00:12:40,079
<i>Same with me.</i>

138
00:12:40,549 --> 00:12:43,484
You told me that...

139
00:12:43,919 --> 00:12:48,219
You'll be the best Ninja in the village,
and make everyone respect you.

140
00:12:49,525 --> 00:12:53,791
If someone comes along and
accepts you for who you are,

141
00:12:53,863 --> 00:12:58,562
no one could be more important
to you than that person.

142
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:04,970
Even though he knew I was from
a clan with Kekkei Genkai,

143
00:13:05,041 --> 00:13:07,601
Zabuza took me in.

144
00:13:08,077 --> 00:13:14,175
My power that everyone hated...
He wanted it, needed it.

145
00:13:15,351 --> 00:13:22,257
<i>Brats like you won't be needed</i>
<i>by anyone and die like dogs.</i>

146
00:13:26,896 --> 00:13:30,457
<i>You have the same eyes</i>
<i>as I do...</i>

147
00:13:37,373 --> 00:13:38,397
<i>Brat...</i>

148
00:13:39,308 --> 00:13:42,937
<i>Do you want...</i>
<i>to be needed by someone?</i>

149
00:13:45,147 --> 00:13:49,277
<i>Are you willing</i>
<i>to give everything for me?</i>

150
00:13:59,862 --> 00:14:03,798
<i>From now on,</i>
<i>your power belongs to me.</i>

151
00:14:18,848 --> 00:14:20,110
<i>Come with me.</i>

152
00:14:26,122 --> 00:14:27,384
I was so happy...

153
00:14:29,658 --> 00:14:31,489
<i>Haku, bad news.</i>

154
00:14:32,828 --> 00:14:35,956
<i>I have to leave the Land of Water</i>
<i>as of tonight.</i>

155
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:41,761
<i>However, I'll be back in</i>
<i>this land some day.</i>

156
00:14:42,571 --> 00:14:44,801
<i>I will rule over this land.</i>

157
00:14:45,674 --> 00:14:47,369
<i>To do that...</i>

158
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:52,072
<i>what I need isn't consolation,</i>
<i>encouragement or empty words.</i>

159
00:14:53,082 --> 00:14:54,811
<i>What I really need is...</i>

160
00:14:54,884 --> 00:14:56,010
<i>I already know.</i>

161
00:14:56,185 --> 00:14:57,584
<i>You have nothing to fear.</i>

162
00:14:57,887 --> 00:15:00,253
<i>I am your weapon, Zabuza.</i>

163
00:15:00,389 --> 00:15:04,723
<i>Keep me by you as a mere tool</i>
<i>that heeds your every word.</i>

164
00:15:07,329 --> 00:15:08,591
<i>You're a good boy!</i>

165
00:15:10,766 --> 00:15:12,859
I apologize, Zabuza.

166
00:15:13,502 --> 00:15:17,233
I wasn't good enough to be
the tool you were looking for.

167
00:15:26,448 --> 00:15:27,676
Naruto!

168
00:15:29,885 --> 00:15:31,079
I want you...

169
00:15:32,655 --> 00:15:34,088
to kill me.

170
00:15:42,166 --> 00:15:46,102
Ninja Art, Summoning,
Earth Style: Fanged Pursuit Jutsu!

171
00:15:53,878 --> 00:15:56,108
Whatever you do won't work!

172
00:15:56,347 --> 00:16:00,010
You have absolutely no idea
where I am now.

173
00:16:00,251 --> 00:16:01,218
However...

174
00:16:02,787 --> 00:16:06,245
I know exactly where you are
and what you're about.

175
00:16:06,691 --> 00:16:07,680
Kakashi...

176
00:16:08,826 --> 00:16:12,023
You are completely
in my hands now.

177
00:16:27,011 --> 00:16:28,876
W-What is that racket?

178
00:16:29,147 --> 00:16:31,980
What... Just what's going on out there?

179
00:16:37,021 --> 00:16:39,956
If you can't use your eyes or ears,
simply use your nose.

180
00:16:41,692 --> 00:16:42,886
That's what happens

181
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:45,724
when you're closing your eyes
in the midst of fog.

182
00:16:45,963 --> 00:16:48,989
This is the Summoning Jutsu
specialized for pursuit.

183
00:16:51,002 --> 00:16:53,596
I deliberately shed my own blood

184
00:16:53,671 --> 00:16:56,139
to stop your attacks both times
for this.

185
00:16:56,808 --> 00:17:01,006
Your weapons have a thick scent of
my blood on them now.

186
00:17:01,546 --> 00:17:04,947
Those are my adorable Ninja Dogs.

187
00:17:05,316 --> 00:17:07,147
And their sense of smell
is without equal.

188
00:17:07,718 --> 00:17:10,414
You're the one who
was playing into my hands.

189
00:17:13,491 --> 00:17:15,550
The fog has lifted already.

190
00:17:16,093 --> 00:17:19,426
And your future is...
death.

191
00:17:21,098 --> 00:17:22,895
I've had enough of your bluffs!

192
00:17:23,467 --> 00:17:24,525
Don't act tough!

193
00:17:25,336 --> 00:17:28,396
There's nothing you can do
in this situation.

194
00:17:28,973 --> 00:17:31,100
Your death is certain.

195
00:17:33,311 --> 00:17:34,369
Zabuza.

196
00:17:34,645 --> 00:17:36,476
You were too full of yourself.

197
00:17:37,315 --> 00:17:39,715
You're too ambitious
for your own good.

198
00:17:49,861 --> 00:17:53,922
You assassinated the Mizukage,
but failed to pull off a coup.

199
00:17:55,967 --> 00:17:58,458
You left the service with
few men under you,

200
00:17:58,536 --> 00:18:00,595
and became a Rogue Ninja.

201
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:05,531
Soon after, your name reached
our Hidden Leaf Village.

202
00:18:06,344 --> 00:18:08,369
You needed to raise funds
to strike back.

203
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,677
And you needed to hide from

204
00:18:10,748 --> 00:18:12,409
the Tracking Unit's
pursuit and retaliation.

205
00:18:13,017 --> 00:18:14,575
Isn't that about the reason

206
00:18:14,652 --> 00:18:18,053
why you hired yourself out
to scum like Gato?

207
00:18:19,523 --> 00:18:20,285
Zabuza.

208
00:18:20,591 --> 00:18:24,652
Do you really believe I've managed
to survive with just Sharingan?

209
00:18:26,130 --> 00:18:30,658
Here's something I didn't copy,
a Jutsu of my own...

210
00:18:31,769 --> 00:18:33,066
To enlighten you!

211
00:18:46,851 --> 00:18:47,783
Lightning Blade!

212
00:18:48,786 --> 00:18:49,878
<i>What the...?!</i>

213
00:18:50,388 --> 00:18:53,619
<i>His hand is visibly overflowing</i>
<i>with Chakra!</i>

214
00:18:56,527 --> 00:18:58,552
You are too dangerous.

215
00:18:59,230 --> 00:19:01,994
Tazuna, the man you are trying
to assassinate

216
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,726
is the symbol of courage in this land!

217
00:19:04,568 --> 00:19:08,231
The bridge he is building
is the hope of this land!

218
00:19:08,739 --> 00:19:11,867
And your ambitions will sacrifice
countless lives.

219
00:19:12,777 --> 00:19:16,736
That isn't how a Shinobi
is supposed to behave.

220
00:19:17,448 --> 00:19:18,506
Who cares?

221
00:19:20,451 --> 00:19:23,943
I have always fought
for my own ideals.

222
00:19:24,989 --> 00:19:28,755
And that will never ever change!

223
00:19:32,330 --> 00:19:33,763
I'll say it again.

224
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:34,893
Huh?

225
00:19:35,466 --> 00:19:36,831
Give up.

226
00:19:40,504 --> 00:19:43,200
Your future is...
death!

227
00:19:45,176 --> 00:19:46,370
Please kill me.

228
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:51,171
What are you hesitating for?

229
00:19:52,416 --> 00:19:53,906
No...

230
00:19:53,985 --> 00:19:56,681
What you said is ridiculous!

231
00:19:57,021 --> 00:19:59,114
You're a weapon?
Just a tool for him?

232
00:19:59,790 --> 00:20:02,554
How can you call him
special to you?

233
00:20:02,626 --> 00:20:05,151
Are you really okay with that?

234
00:20:07,098 --> 00:20:08,122
Is that wrong?

235
00:20:08,466 --> 00:20:09,091
Huh?

236
00:20:10,101 --> 00:20:12,433
Tell me, what is wrong with that?

237
00:20:12,837 --> 00:20:13,804
Well, uh...

238
00:20:14,405 --> 00:20:15,372
It's not...

239
00:20:16,574 --> 00:20:20,408
Zabuza counts on me,
even if I'm worthless.

240
00:20:21,445 --> 00:20:23,003
He made me feel needed.

241
00:20:54,412 --> 00:20:59,076
But now, I've lost my usefulness
that affirmed my existence.

242
00:21:00,518 --> 00:21:04,079
Zabuza no longer needs me.

243
00:21:08,426 --> 00:21:11,691
That's why,
I am now appealing to you.

244
00:21:14,732 --> 00:21:16,962
Please, make it quick

245
00:22:51,965 --> 00:22:55,526
W-Why did this happen?

246
00:22:56,670 --> 00:23:00,774
Is this what it means to
be a strong Ninja?

247
00:23:00,774 --> 00:23:02,901
To protect someone?

248
00:23:03,576 --> 00:23:05,441
Are you okay with that?

249
